<TITLE> Prime Finance to launch mutual fund </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 02 (bdnews24.com)--Leading merchant bank Prime Finance is likely to launch its Tk 200 million mutual fund this year, according to a statement released Saturday. The Prime Finance First Mutual Fund, aimed at the growing needs of Bangladeshi investors, was registered following the recent signing of a trust deed between the sponsors Prime Finance and trustee Investment Corporation of Bangladesh. Twenty percent of the fund, or Tk 40 million, will be sponsored by Prime Finance itself, while another 30 percent, or Tk 60 million, will be raised through private placement. The other 50 percent, or Tk 100 million, will be raised from the market by an initial public offering. ICB will act as the fund's trustee and custodian while ICB Asset Management Company Ltd will be responsible for managing the fund. Announcing the upcoming launch of the fund, managing director of Prime Finance Md Akter H Sannamat said: "The recent market situation has boosted investor demand for products which gravitate towards safer investment." ICB Asset Management Company Ltd will soon submit a prospectus with market regulator the Securities and Exchange Commission to invite public subscription, Sannamat added. Twenty million shares have been divided into market lots of 500 that will be offered to investors at a face value of Tk 10 each. bdn
